{"author":{"id":"1e0a6ff3e01313072cf7b3803c158c22d01a37717237fe198e814e781752b172"},"ops":[{"type":3,"timestamp":1781104705,"nonce":"KPIFH9EveyNIna3D+wwvqTpuQno=","message":"Fixed on feature/merge-take-skip-aware (commit 38de0d9).\n\nThe merge take path was the only one that ignored skip state: it always built the am-mbox from every commit on the review branch, so selecting merge with skipped patches silently pulled them back in, and there was no way to keep the cover letter while dropping them.\n\nThe fix makes merge skip-aware:\n- When some patches are skipped, the merge method now routes through the patch picker (skipped patches pre-deselected), so you can produce a cover-letter merge commit that excludes them. A series with nothing skipped still merges whole without an extra prompt.\n- The chosen method is preserved through the picker, so a skip-trimmed merge stays a real merge commit rather than becoming a flat cherry-pick.\n- The cherry-pick selection is threaded into _do_take_merge, _prepare_am_messages, and _record_take_metadata, and only the merged patches are counted in the merge-commit template.\n\nNo merge-topology changes were needed: the merge path already builds FETCH_HEAD from the am-mbox and merges that, so filtering the mbox is sufficient. Covered by new tests in TestMergeTakeSkipRouting; full tui + three-way-merge suites pass (111 tests).","files":null}]}